We’re so excited to announce our second Facebook show, featuring our favorite Mother-Son duo of Emma and Mama Rosa!! Join us each week as Emma takes his mom to the movies to get her unfiltered review. Check out Episode 1 where they go watch Terminator 2 in 3D!

We don’t often talk about what we do - we prefer to just go do it. But given the context of everything going on in our country, we think it’s more important than ever before to have content by Latinos, for Latinos, that tells our stories, that represents us in media so we can get beyond the stereotypes and fear mongering. To show a mother and son who just have fun at the movies.

Please like Mom’s Movie Review to get each new episode. We are so grateful for our fans and your continued support!!
headline: Mom's Movie Review

mitú fans! We’re so proud today to launch Episode 1 of What's Good in Your Hood featuring Guerilla Tacos in #DTLA -- We created this show because of the overwhelming response you have had to our food content. We didn’t just want to showcase Latino foods, but the people who are transforming their communities through food.

This is part of Facebook’s new shows program, and we’re glad they are investing in the creation of content for Latinos. But we need your support to make it the best it can be - so please Like the What’s Good In Your Hood page for new episodes each week, and send us your feedback, share with friends, and let us know that joint in your hood we need to be showcasing!
